description:
Why 4 stars
- Boudin Blanc. The sausage was very well cooked - it tasted somewhat between normal sausage and normal meat. Meanwhile, it was very juicy;

Why not 5 stars
- Other than Boudin Blanc, everything else was average;
- Steak tartare: there is nothing sparkling about the starter. We were consulted before it was mixed regarding how spicy we would like it to me. It is good to see all the ingredients there before they became part of the dish;
- Coq au vin: The chicken was well cooked - the meat was very tender, and the sauce was good. But again, there is nothing special.

Side note
- The setting is touristy, to some extent, given that the look of the outdoor part of the restaurant;
- The indoor part of the restaurant is well decorated, very romantic; the outdoor part is in the alley - it was clean and is worth trying;
